page-chat-card-a-body = The shell keeps the conversation lane readable, with room for streamed turns and operator follow-up.
page-chat-card-b-title = Tool-aware framing
page-chat-card-b-body = Route copy acknowledges research, code, and document work without pretending that hidden tools are live.
page-chat-card-c-title = Review-first posture
page-chat-card-c-body = Status copy stays literal so maintainers can see whether the shell is in preview or backed by the runtime.

route-memory-label = Memory
page-memory-summary = Browse retained notes, inspect hierarchy, and hold editing behind an explicit feature seam.
page-memory-mode = Read-focused preview
page-memory-status = Edit actions gated
page-memory-agenda = Keep breadcrumb context, search intent, and note readability consistent across large trees and small screens.
page-memory-guardrail = Editing remains hidden until the write contract and conflict handling are confirmed by the backend.
page-memory-card-a-title = Tree context
page-memory-card-a-body = The route keeps the sense of nested memory without requiring the old multi-page sidebar runtime.
page-memory-card-b-title = Readability first
page-memory-card-b-body = Dense notes stay legible with semantic panels, restrained contrast, and document-level direction metadata.
page-memory-card-c-title = Safe mutation seam
page-memory-card-c-body = Feature flags make the difference between read-only preview and future editable memory explicit.

